n Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Hungarian Geza, Jeno, Arpad, Attila, Csaba.","Hungarian: variant of   Papp  , meaning ‘priest (of the Catholic or Orthodox Church)’. This surname is also found in Romania, Slovakia, Croatia, and Serbia, and also among Rusyns (in Serbia and Croatia). See also   Pop   2 and   Popa  .","English: variant of   Pape   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Papp","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Hungarian Laszlo, Zoltan, Geza, Istvan, Gabor, Miklos, Tibor, Arpad, Denes, Imre, Attila.","German (Bavaria, Tyrol): from Middle High German <i>pap</i> ‘baby food’, Dutch <i>pap</i> ‘porridge, pap’, hence perhaps a nickname denoting someone who had lost his teeth or subsisted on a meager diet.","Hungarian: from <i>pap</i> ‘priest (of the Catholic or Orthodox Church)’, probably an occupational name for someone in the service of a priest or a nickname for a pious person. This surname is also found in Romania and Slovakia, and also among Rusyns. Compare   Pap   and   Pop  ."]}]},{"name":"Gruffudd","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Welsh: traditional spelling of   Griffith  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Griffith","meanings":["Welsh (Carmarthenshire and western England): from the Old Welsh personal name <i>Gruffudd</i>, Old Welsh <i>Grip(p)iud</i>, composed of the elements <i>grip</i>, of uncertain significance, + <i>iud</i> ‘chief, lord’."]}]},{"name":"Morgan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of Welsh Morcant , traditionally a boy's name. In Britain since the late 1990s the name has become equally popular as a girl's name, perhaps adopted with conscious reference to  King Arthur's  jealous stepsister  Morgan le Fay . Elsewhere in the English-speaking world, especially in North America, where it also enjoys considerable popularity, it is used predominantly for girls."],"variants":[{"name":"Morcant","meanings":["Traditional: composed of an unexplained first element + a second representing the Old Celtic element <i>cant</i> ‘circle; completion’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Morgan ap Gruffudd was born about 1380, in Llandinam, Montgomeryshire, Wales. She had at least 1 daughter with Morgan ap Gruffudd."},"et":{"about 1380–":"umbes 1380–Surnud","1380–Male":"1380–Surnud","1395–Female":"1395–Surnud","1380–Female":"1380–Surnud","about 1380":"umbes 1380","1395":"1395","abt 1395":"umbes 1395","1380":"1380","of Glyn-Nedd, Glmrgn, Wls":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Llandinam, Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Llandinam, Montgomeryshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1380–":"noin 1380–Kuollut","1380–Male":"1380–Kuollut","1395–Female":"1395–Kuollut","1380–Female":"1380–Kuollut","about 1380":"noin 1380","1395":"1395","abt 1395":"noin 1395","1380":"1380","of Glyn-Nedd, Glmrgn, Wls":"Glamorgan, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Llandinam, Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Llandinam, Montgomeryshire, Wales"},"fr":{"about 1380–":"environ 1380–Décédée","1380–Male":"1380–Décédé","1395–Female":"1395–Décédée","1380–Female":"1380–Décédée","about 1380":"environ 1380","1395":"1395","abt 1395":"environ 1395","1380":"1380","of Glyn-Nedd, Glmrgn, Wls":"Glamorgan, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Llandinam, Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Llandinam, Montgomeryshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Morgan ap Gruffudd est née environ 1380, à Llandinam, Montgomeryshire, Galles. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Morgan ap Gruffudd."},"de":{"about 1380–":"um 1380–Verstorben","1380–Male":"1380–Verstorben","1395–Female":"1395–Verstorben","1380–Female":"1380–Verstorben","about 1380":"um 1380","1395":"1395","abt 1395":"um 1395","1380":"1380","of Glyn-Nedd, Glmrgn, Wls":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Llandinam, Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Llandinam, Montgomeryshire, Wales","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Morgan ap Gruffudd wurde um 1380 in Llandinam, 